data.title: History of Philippine Politics, Governments and Constitutions
data.meta_description: HISTORY-OF-PHILIPPINE-POLITICS-AND-GOVERNMENTS_-RIPH111-FINALS-LECTURE-2 - Free download as Powerpoint Presentation (.ppt / .pptx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or view presentation slides online. The document provides a detailed history of politics and governments in the Philippines from pre-Hispanic times up until the establishment of the First Philippine Republic in 1898. It describes the barangay system of self-governance, the Spanish colonial period starting in 1521 and various Filipino revolts against Spanish rule, the revolutionary movements in the late 1800s leading to independence in 1898, and the establishment of the First Republic and subsequent conflict with the United States.
